{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"coaching":[{"coaching":"Pin down escape-hatch condition in Gerrit-side AC with a concrete worked example.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f2a2d1fb5a66522f6"],"move_id":"6","move_name":"specification by example","subject":"escape-hatch condition in Gerrit-side AC"},{"coaching":"Plan how acceptance-criteria verification approach will be verified in-session — restate any deferred or unobservable success target as an observable proxy.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f607dd457c67f9209"],"move_id":"9","move_name":"plan the verification","subject":"acceptance-criteria verification approach"},{"coaching":"State the concrete attestation evidence the [operator-attested] enforce_since qualification across plan sections will require (a change id / vote outcome / timestamp), recorded on the ticket.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["fb7e6ecf2d1c99840"],"move_id":"14","move_name":"state attestation evidence","subject":"enforce_since qualification across plan sections"},{"coaching":"Test the riskiest assumption behind full-history grandfathering exit-zero assumption first.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["fe4620a7e0ced8703"],"move_id":"4","move_name":"riskiest-assumption test","subject":"full-history grandfathering exit-zero assumption"},{"coaching":"Record an ADR for anchor-SHA dependency ordering across child stories — it reads like a one-way door.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f6e89c817ab0325fb"],"move_id":"8","move_name":"ADR / one-way-door","subject":"anchor-SHA dependency ordering across child stories"}],"coverage":{"counts":{"advisory_overflow":0,"advisory_surfaced":3,"blocking":0,"dropped":15,"indeterminate":0},"det":{"P1":{"ac_items":5,"blocking":false,"clarity_score":7,"name":"readiness-shape","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P2":{"blocking":false,"name":"resolution","probed":1,"ran":true,"references":1,"resolved":1,"status":"pass","unresolved_or_abstained":0},"P3":{"blocking":false,"name":"package-existence","packages":0,"ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P4":{"ac_items":5,"blocking":false,"desc_chars":5150,"file_impact":5,"name":"oversize","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P5":{"blocking":false,"children":5,"edges":4,"name":"task-dag","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P6":{"ac_items":5,"blocking":false,"name":"ac-quality","ran":true,"status":"fail","verify_commands_linted":39,"verify_lint_abstained":39},"P7":{"blocking":false,"destructive_hits":[],"name":"destructive-sniff","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P8":{"blocking":false,"budget_tokens":868000,"name":"reviewability","plan_tokens":1315,"ran":true,"status":"pass","worst_parent_child_pair_tokens":1995},"P9":{"applicable":false,"blocking":false,"file_impact":5,"name":"file-impact-coverage","ran":true,"status":"pass"}},"floored_criteria":["E1","G4"],"floored_finding_ids":["fb7e6ecf2d1c99840","f6e89c817ab0325fb"],"llm_ran":true,"metrics":{"claim_path":"no-llm/no-network (structural; the fast claim check is a local HMAC verify)","det_ms":340.3,"llm_calls":22,"llm_ms":414498.7,"total_ms":414955.1,"verify_requests":13},"narrowed":true,"remediation":{"baseline":"signature","eligible":true,"reasons":{"code_unchanged":true,"plan_changed":true,"prior_sidecar":true,"registry_unchanged":true,"signed":true,"within_window":true}},"routing":{"agent_tier":["G3","G4","G6","T1","T10","T11","T13","T14","T3","T5c","T8"],"single_turn":["COH","E1","E2","E3","F1","F4","G5","T12","T2","T4","T5e"]}},"findings":[{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Align parent AC1(c) and AC3 with the child 1a51 conditional: either (a) update parent criteria to explicitly allow the 'no in-scope Gerrit writer' documentation path as a valid proof, or (b) require child 1a51 to produce a signed event unconditionally (e.g., using an inbound-translation write as the canary) rather than permitting the escape hatch.","cohort":["G3","G4"],"criteria":["G3"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Child 1a51 AC: 'the canary is re-run on the deployed VM for the in-scope path; the signed event id / log (or a documented \"no in-scope Gerrit-side writer exists\") is recorded on this ticket.'","Child 8d39 AC: 'the Gerrit-side writer iff story 3 classified one (if story 3 found no in-scope Gerrit writer, that surface is satisfied by its documented classification instead).'","Parent AC1: 'a representative ticket write from each of (a) … (b) … and (c) a Gerrit-side operation that writes tickets … each produces a signed event and is accepted.'","Parent AC3: 'Each of the three writer surfaces has a persistent signing key configured (local per-machine key, populated REBAR_BOT_SIGNING_KEY CI secret, Gerrit-side service key).'","container pairing: parent + 1a51-b170-5168-46d2/4dc0-d003-c236-45de/79da-c7e4-8d7c-471d/8d39-85d7-8f34-45e6/8d91-5103-ae1b-44a7"],"finding":"Child 1a51 introduces a conditional escape hatch ('no in-scope Gerrit-side writer exists → document the classification') that is not reflected in the parent's unconditional phrasing of AC1(c) and AC3. Parent AC1 states that 'a Gerrit-side operation that writes tickets … produces a signed event' as one of the three mandatory proofs; parent AC3 states 'each of the three writer surfaces has a persistent signing key.' Neither parent criterion accommodates the case where zero in-scope Gerrit writers are found. This is a bypass-annotation pattern: child 1a51 could close itself by annotating Gerrit as 'non-writing/exempt' — satisfying the child's own AC — while leaving the parent AC with an uncovered surface, and child 8d39 mirrors this with its own 'iff story 3 classified one' conditional.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f2a2d1fb5a66522f6","impact":0.85,"is_primary":null,"location":"child 1a51-b170-5168-46d2, AC bullet 4 ('or a documented no in-scope Gerrit-side writer exists'); parent AC1(c) and AC3","norm_id":"nc73fa289afad9a20","priority":0.85,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["Child 1a51 closes with 'no in-scope Gerrit writer' documentation; parent AC1(c) and AC3 remain uncovered for the Gerrit surface; child 8d39 reaches 'enforcement' with no Gerrit-side signed event ever having been produced, yet the epic is marked complete.","If a Gerrit reconciler does write work tickets but is misclassified as exempt or non-writing, the bypass annotation silently hides the gap."],"severity":"critical","suggested_fix":"Add to the parent AC1(c) parenthetical: '… or, if the Gerrit classification confirms zero in-scope writers, a verified non-writing/exempt classification with file/line evidence constitutes coverage — record this explicitly.' Update AC3 to mirror the same conditional so both criteria use the same escape valve uniformly.","tier":"LLM","validity":1.0,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"low","internal_conflict":"medium","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"medium","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":null,"blocking_enabled":null,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["P6"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["2 criterion line(s) bundle multiple deliverables with 'and' (split so each is independently verifiable).","vague/subjective terms present: clean"],"finding":"Acceptance-criteria / definition-of-done quality issues.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f607dd457c67f9209","impact":0.4,"is_primary":null,"location":"","norm_id":"ned06ebc801a522e3","priority":0.4,"reason":null,"scenarios":[],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Split compound criteria, replace subjective terms with observable outcomes, and state how each is verified.","tier":"DET","validity":1.0,"verification":null},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add an explicit AC step to child 8d39 requiring a post-pin `rebar verify-identity` full-history scan (exit 0, zero pre-boundary flagged) immediately after `enforce_since` is written to `rebar.toml`, so the written value is confirmed — not just the chosen value.","cohort":["G3","G4"],"criteria":["G3"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Parent AC2: 'rebar verify-identity over the full history exits 0 with zero pre-boundary events flagged. Proof: … a synthetic UNSIGNED event dated before the boundary passes the gate.'","Child 8d91 AC bullet 1: 'rebar verify-identity over the full history exits 0 with zero pre-boundary events flagged, using the chosen anchor.' — this runs before enforce_since is written to rebar.toml.","Child 8d39 AC: lists enforcement real (non-zero on unsigned), per-surface pass, and rollback — no mention of re-running full history scan post-pin.","Child 8d91 explicitly states: 'rebar.toml is NOT modified by this story.'","container pairing: parent + 1a51-b170-5168-46d2/4dc0-d003-c236-45de/79da-c7e4-8d7c-471d/8d39-85d7-8f34-45e6/8d91-5103-ae1b-44a7"],"finding":"Parent AC2 requires that after `enforce_since` is pinned, `rebar verify-identity` over the FULL HISTORY exits 0 with zero pre-boundary events flagged. Child 8d91 verifies the grandfathering logic and regression test using the CHOSEN (but not yet written) SHA, while child 8d39 writes the SHA into `rebar.toml` but does not explicitly include a post-pin full-history re-run in its acceptance criteria. The remainder — confirming zero pre-boundary flags after the value is actually written — is unassigned to any child.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fe4620a7e0ced8703","impact":0.264,"is_primary":null,"location":"child 8d91-5103-ae1b-44a7 AC bullet 1; child 8d39-85d7-8f34-45e6 AC; parent AC2","norm_id":"n05772cca8ffa699b","priority":0.132,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["Child 8d91 verifies grandfathering with the chosen SHA in isolation; child 8d39 writes a different SHA (typo, wrong commit) into rebar.toml; no child re-verifies the full history scan after the write — the bug is undetected until enforcement is live.","A late change to the anchor SHA between 8d91 and 8d39 (e.g., because additional signing commits land) could invalidate 8d91's verification without triggering a re-check."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"In child 8d39's AC, add: '[ ] After writing enforce_since to rebar.toml, run rebar verify-identity over the full history and confirm exit 0 with zero pre-boundary events flagged — proving the written SHA, not just the chosen SHA, correctly grandfathers all historical events.'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.5,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"low","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] State the chosen signing-key provisioning mechanism for local sessions (e.g., 'use `identity.signing_key` in the per-machine rebar config') so the executor has a single unambiguous path.","cohort":["E2","F1"],"criteria":["E2"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["'provision a persistent signing key for local worktrees/sessions (per-machine `identity.signing_key` or exported `REBAR_IDENTITY_SIGNING_KEY`)'","Three mechanisms named with 'or' connective but no stated default or selection criterion","The plan's Context section confirms all three are currently absent ('no identity.signing_key, no REBAR_IDENTITY_SIGNING_KEY, no .rebar/current_identity') — executor cannot infer which was intended"],"finding":"Story 1 lists three distinct signing-key provisioning mechanisms (per-machine `identity.signing_key` config, exported `REBAR_IDENTITY_SIGNING_KEY` env var, `.rebar/current_identity`) without choosing among them. These are not equivalent in persistence, scope, or security posture, so the executor must make a real design decision that the plan defers.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f2dc30cff3d5160fd","impact":0.264,"is_primary":null,"location":"Scope / planned child stories — Story 1: 'Local machine signing'","norm_id":"n29b146ea838f101b","priority":0.099,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["An executor implementing Story 1 must independently decide whether to write config, set an env var, or write a .rebar file — different implications for CI, shell profile, and multi-worktree setups.","If the wrong mechanism is chosen, downstream Stories 3–5 may need to be revisited."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Select one mechanism and state it as the plan decision: e.g., 'Provision a persistent ed25519 signing key and register it via `identity.signing_key` in the per-machine rebar config (~/.rebar/config or equivalent); `REBAR_IDENTITY_SIGNING_KEY` is the fallback for headless sessions only.'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.375,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add an AC bullet (or extend AC bullet 2) that explicitly requires the boundary regression test to exist as a committed artifact (e.g., a named test case in the test suite or a CI job step) verifiable via `git log` or test-runner output, not only a one-time manual proof.","cohort":["COH","E1"],"criteria":["E1"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Scope story 4: 'add/confirm a regression test around the boundary'","AC bullet 2 proof: 'a synthetic UNSIGNED event dated before the boundary passes the gate, while a new unsigned/forged in-scope event AFTER the boundary FAILS it' — describes a manual run, not a committed test"],"finding":"Story 4 explicitly lists 'add/confirm a regression test around the boundary' as a deliverable, but no AC bullet verifies that a regression test *artifact* (automated test, test file, or committed script) exists or is merged. AC bullet 2's proof only describes a manual demonstration (run a synthetic event before/after the boundary), which does not confirm a persistent regression guard is in place.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f8221f1ddfb194c51","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Scope story 4; AC bullet 2","norm_id":"nb8afdf67d7fd1a57","priority":0.0,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":["The boundary regression test is demonstrated once manually but never committed; a future refactor silently breaks the grandfathering logic with no automated guard to catch it."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Extend AC bullet 2's proof to include: 'The boundary regression test is present in the test suite and passes in CI (verifiable via `rebar show` on the story-4 change and the CI run log).'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.25,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"no","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add an explicit rollback/back-out procedure to story 5: document that if post-flip verification fails, `identity.require_authenticated` is immediately reverted to `false` (or `advisory`) in a follow-on change, and specify the trigger condition (e.g., any writer surface producing a gate-red event) and who is authorized to revert.","cohort":["T2","T4"],"criteria":["T4"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["'set `identity.require_authenticated = true` + the pinned `enforce_since` in ONE change' — no revert path stated","'after it, `verify-identity` demonstrably FAILS on a new in-scope unsigned/forged event' — enforcement is confirmed live, but no back-out if confirmation was incomplete","ABSENCE: no section describes how to revert the flag or what constitutes a safe rollback trigger"],"finding":"The enforcement flip (`identity.require_authenticated = true`) is called 'atomic' and 'enforcing' but the plan provides no explicit rollback/back-out procedure if post-flip a writer surface is discovered to be unsigned or if the enforcement produces unexpected failures. The T4 criterion requires not just acknowledgement of the breaking change but an explicit reversibility mechanism.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f3ffa902d06bcfc61","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Planned child story 5 ('The atomic flip') and AC: 'The flip is atomic and enforcing'","norm_id":"n20e20875aa8432fe","priority":0.0,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":["A writer surface (e.g., Gerrit opcert-service) was believed to be signing but was not; post-flip every ticket write from that surface fails the gate until the key is confirmed — with no documented revert procedure the team must improvise under pressure","The `enforce_since` boundary is set incorrectly and legitimate historical events start failing — reverting requires knowing exactly which config knob to touch and in what order"],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Add a subsection under story 5: 'Rollback plan: if `verify-identity` exits non-zero on any writer surface after the flip, immediately open a revert change setting `require_authenticated = false` (returning to advisory mode) before any further investigation. Re-run stories 1–4 confirmations before re-attempting the flip.'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.25,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"no","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add an ADR or CLAUDE.md section capturing the atomic-flip pattern: the invariant that `require_authenticated` must only flip after all writer surfaces are signing, the role of `enforce_since` as the grandfather boundary, and the procedure for re-pinning it on future enforcement expansions.","cohort":["T12","T5e"],"criteria":["T5e"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan defines the pattern: 'the flip must land AFTER every writer signs, in the same change that pins enforce_since'","No mention of an ADR, CLAUDE.md update, or design-doc entry anywhere in the plan","Novel decision: how enforce_since is meant to be re-used/re-pinned in future enforcement expansions is not documented"],"finding":"The plan introduces the 'atomic flip with enforce_since grandfather boundary' as an architectural enforcement pattern but does not call for capturing this decision in an ADR, CLAUDE.md, or design doc. Future maintainers inheriting the system will have no recorded rationale for why enforce_since exists, how to re-pin it on future enforcement expansions, or what the invariant is between require_authenticated and enforce_since.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f12c9942ab39e7da5","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"## Scope / planned child stories — Story 4 (Grandfathering remediation) and Story 5 (The atomic flip)","norm_id":"n122d1ca1a61fe569","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["A future maintainer needs to expand enforcement (e.g., add a new writer surface) and must re-pin enforce_since — without a doc, they may not understand the invariant or the required sequencing","Key rotation or identity system changes may require re-understanding the grandfather semantics"],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"In CLAUDE.md or a new doc/adr/identity-enforcement.md, record: (1) the enforce_since invariant and how to re-pin it, (2) the required sequencing (confirm all writers sign → pin enforce_since → flip require_authenticated in one commit), (3) the rollback procedure (flip require_authenticated back to false).","tier":"LLM","validity":0.1429,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"no","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add an explicit rollback procedure to Story 5 / the success criteria: specify that reverting `require_authenticated` to `false` (and unfreezing `enforce_since` if needed) is the immediate mitigation, document it as a one-commit revert, and add a rollback-readiness AC (e.g., a dry-run revert is staged/tested before the flip lands).","cohort":["T12","T5e"],"criteria":["T12"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["'Flipping the flag today would fail every push because the store is unsigned' — shows the blast radius of a bad flip","AC states the flip must be atomic but does not pair it with a rollback AC","No mention anywhere in the plan of: how to revert the flag, what a rollback commit looks like, or who is authorized to execute it","The plan notes enforce_since must be pinned in the same change — a revert must also un-pin it correctly"],"finding":"The plan has no explicit rollback procedure for the enforcement-flag flip. If `require_authenticated = true` causes unexpected failures after merge (e.g., a writer's signing key is lost or a new unsigned writer surface is discovered), there is no documented, tested path to quickly undo the change — especially given the plan's own warning that 'flipping the flag today would fail every push.'","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f2d021b8a424517ad","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"## Scope / planned child stories — Story 5 (The atomic flip); Acceptance Criteria — 'The flip is atomic and enforcing'","norm_id":"n9b5b6f1d7c2d2028","priority":0.0,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":["A signing key is accidentally rotated or lost after the flip, causing a writer surface to produce unsigned events that now fail the gate — every push is red until someone discovers and executes an undocumented revert","A previously unknown writer surface (e.g., an automated script) is discovered post-flip producing unsigned events"],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Add a 'Rollback plan' subsection to Story 5: 'To undo: revert the single commit (or push a follow-up that sets require_authenticated = false); no data cleanup is required because pre-flip events are grandfathered. A staged revert commit should be authored and reviewed alongside the flip PR so it can be merged immediately if needed.'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.25,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"no","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Clarify the AC 2 proof mechanism: specify whether the 'synthetic UNSIGNED event before the boundary' is validated via (a) a dedicated unit/integration test on a synthetic git store (the correct approach, since the live tracker cannot have commits retroactively inserted before ce3f8bc) or (b) pointing to the existing test suite (e.g., test_verify_authorship grandfathering tests), and update the AC accordingly.","cohort":["G6"],"criteria":["G6"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan AC: 'a synthetic UNSIGNED event dated before the boundary passes the gate, while a new unsigned/forged in-scope event AFTER the boundary FAILS it'","_is_enforced() in verify_authorship.py:262-282 uses git merge-base --is-ancestor(since_ref, commit_sha) — ancestry on the tracker branch, not event timestamps","enforce_since is already pinned to ce3f8bcbe13d37e93a0758f7f73cb3ebeac3b043 in rebar.toml; creating a tracker commit ancestrally before this ref requires history rewriting on the tracker branch"],"finding":"AC bullet 2 requires proof via 'a synthetic UNSIGNED event dated before the boundary passes the gate' but the plan specifies no mechanism for constructing this proof artifact. The enforce_since boundary is commit-ancestry-based (git merge-base --is-ancestor on the TRACKER branch), not wall-clock time-based — so 'dating' an event before the boundary means having a tracker-branch commit that is an ancestor of the enforce_since ref, which requires either (a) retroactively inserting a commit before ce3f8bc (impossible without rewriting history) or (b) relying on a test fixture / synthetic store not the live tracker. Without a stated mechanism, an implementer may attempt a wall-clock timestamp approach that does not satisfy the gate logic, or may skip the proof entirely.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f5807d6593f9b16e9","impact":0.44,"is_primary":null,"location":"Acceptance Criteria — 'Pre-flip events are grandfathered' bullet; specifically 'Proof: a synthetic UNSIGNED event dated before the boundary passes the gate'","norm_id":"nd7a6db66967429e0","priority":0.165,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":["Implementer creates a synthetic event with an old wall-clock timestamp but commits it to the tracker AFTER the enforce_since boundary — the gate enforces it (it's a descendant of enforce_since), so the proof fails unexpectedly.","Implementer correctly uses a test fixture on a separate git repo/store, but this isn't stated in the plan, leaving it undiscovered or done inconsistently."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Replace 'Proof: a synthetic UNSIGNED event dated before the boundary passes the gate' with 'Proof: the existing grandfathering test suite (e.g., test_identity_ac7_bff8_heldout.py) is run and passes, confirming pre-boundary events are grandfathered; a manual check of rebar verify-identity output on the live store shows no pre-boundary events flagged as enforced.'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.375,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"underspecified_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Correct AC bullet 1(c) and Story 3 to name the **reconciler** (not the review-bot or opcert-service) as the Gerrit-side service whose non-exempt ticket writes must be confirmed as signed and accepted by rebar verify-identity; note that review-bot writes exempt types (attribution-only, not gate-enforced) and opcert-service uses a separate op-cert signing path.","cohort":["G6"],"criteria":["G6"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["ticket 245e: 'the review-bot writes only EXEMPT types (code_review artifacts, review_bot/voter.py), so signing here is for CLEAN ATTRIBUTION (the merge-gate does not require signatures on exempt types), not a hard must-sign'","verify_authorship.py:125: _GATE_EXEMPT_TYPES = (\"session_log\", \"code_review\", \"identity\")","verify_authorship.py:373-376: _is_gate_exempt_ticket() causes code_review tickets to be skipped entirely from _collect_all()","opcert_service/keyprov.py: provisioned_signing_key provisions REBAR_OPCERT_KEY_PATH, not REBAR_IDENTITY_SIGNING_KEY — a separate signing path for op-certs, not authorship events"],"finding":"AC bullet 1(c) names 'a Gerrit-side operation that writes tickets (review-bot / reconciler / opcert-service)' as requiring 'a signed event accepted by rebar verify-identity.' But review-bot writes only gate-exempt ticket types (code_review — confirmed in ticket 245e and _GATE_EXEMPT_TYPES in verify_authorship.py:125). These events are filtered out of verify-identity scope by _is_gate_exempt_ticket() and never appear in its report. So 'verify-identity exits 0' for the review-bot is vacuously true regardless of signing. Similarly, the opcert-service uses a separate signing path (provisioned_signing_key + REBAR_OPCERT_KEY_PATH) for op-cert attestations, not authorship signatures verified by verify-identity. The only non-exempt Gerrit-side writer is the reconciler. Conflating all three services in the AC obscures what must actually be confirmed.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fdab2ca42f72c16d4","impact":0.264,"is_primary":null,"location":"Acceptance Criteria — 'With identity.require_authenticated = true, no writer surface fails' bullet (c); Scope / planned child stories — Story 3 'Gerrit-side signing'","norm_id":"ne6b7611396737b40","priority":0.099,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["Story 3 implementer confirms review-bot 'signs' events (by checking REBAR_IDENTITY_SIGNING_KEY is set) but rebar verify-identity never reports those events anyway; the AC appears satisfied but the meaningful Gerrit-side writer (the reconciler) is not confirmed.","Implementer skips reconciler confirmation because the review-bot is listed first and appears to satisfy the AC."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Update AC (c) to: '(c) a Gerrit-side operation that writes non-exempt tickets (the reconciler / reconcile-bridge on the deployed VM) produces a signed event and is accepted; the review-bot's code_review writes are attribution-only (exempt from the gate by design).'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.375,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"low","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add a brief positive rationale in the Context or Story 5 explaining WHY the provision-then-confirm-then-flip sequence is the chosen approach: specifically, that flipping before all writer surfaces are confirmed signing would immediately fail every push from any unconfirmed surface, and the grandfather boundary only protects historical events — not new unsigned writes from an unconfigured writer.","cohort":["G6"],"criteria":["G6"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan Context: 'Flipping the flag today would fail every push because the store is unsigned — the flip must land AFTER every writer signs, in the same change that pins enforce_since.' — states the constraint but not the positive justification for this ordering vs. alternatives.","ABSENCE: no statement of why enforce_since cannot simply be set to current HEAD (covering all existing events) and require_authenticated flipped now, with the expectation that writers will provision keys reactively."],"finding":"The plan states the sequencing constraint ('the flip must land AFTER every writer signs, in the same change that pins enforce_since') but does not articulate a positive rationale for why this approach is preferred over the structurally different alternative of flipping immediately with enforce_since advanced to cover ALL current events (including post-rollout ones). The implicit reasoning — that confirming signing before flipping avoids any gap where new unsigned writes fail the gate — is the key design insight, but it is left implicit, which means an implementer working from this plan would not understand why Story 4's confirm-then-flip ordering is critical.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fe4ebfbdaea429ff6","impact":0.264,"is_primary":null,"location":"Context section — 'the flip must land AFTER every writer signs, in the same change that pins enforce_since'; no dedicated rationale section","norm_id":"n0f5ff3f96746803a","priority":0.066,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["An implementer or reviewer questions whether Story 4 is redundant (since enforce_since is already set) and collapses Stories 4 and 5, skipping the pre-flip confirmation step that validates signing is actually working on all surfaces."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.25,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"no","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Story 3 must specify exactly how the Gerrit-side service signing key is stored on the deployed VM (e.g., injected via a secrets manager / Vault / SSM Parameter Store, stored in a file with 0600 permissions owned by the service account, never in a config-management repo), and this storage method must be stated in the acceptance criteria for that story.","cohort":["T10"],"criteria":["T10"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["'confirm the deployed review-bot / reconciler / opcert-service signs its ticket writes on the VM'","AC: 'Gerrit-side service key' listed as a required configured persistent key","ABSENCE: no storage mechanism, file permissions, vault/SSM reference, or environment-injection method described for the VM-resident key"],"finding":"The plan provisions signing keys for Gerrit-side services (review-bot / reconciler / opcert-service) on a deployed VM but never specifies how those private keys are stored or protected on the VM — file system path, permissions, vault/SSM integration, or environment injection mechanism are all absent.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f4c105ac170cb2de2","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Scope / planned child stories — Story 3 (Gerrit-side signing)","norm_id":"n2882f4e11c3f7b83","priority":0.0,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":["Private signing key written as plaintext to a world-readable config file or log output on the Gerrit VM","Key leaks via a VM snapshot, backup, or configuration-management repo commit","No way to audit or rotate the key if it is compromised post-flip"],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Add to Story 3 AC: 'The Gerrit-side signing key is stored as an OS-level secret (e.g., systemd credential, HashiCorp Vault, or cloud SSM secret) injected at service start, with file permissions restricted to the service account (mode 0600). It MUST NOT appear in any config-management repository, log output, or world-readable path. Confirm with `stat` and a secrets-audit step in the canary run.'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.375,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"insufficient","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"medium","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add to the epic (or Story 5 AC) a stated policy for key rotation cadence and a revocation/re-keying procedure (e.g., 'keys rotate annually; on suspected compromise, revoke the old identity entry, issue a new key, and re-confirm signing on that surface before the gate is re-enabled').","cohort":["T10"],"criteria":["T10"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["'provision a persistent signing key for local worktrees/sessions'","'populate the REBAR_BOT_SIGNING_KEY secret'","'Gerrit-side service key' — all described as persistent but no rotation cadence or revocation path mentioned"],"finding":"All three provisioned signing keys (local per-machine, REBAR_BOT_SIGNING_KEY CI secret, Gerrit-side VM key) are described as persistent/long-lived with no rotation schedule, expiry policy, or revocation procedure if a key is compromised.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f9136dcbc6043e474","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Scope / planned child stories (all three signing stories) + AC 'Signing is provisioned everywhere before the flip'","norm_id":"n1bd99438f88a1a07","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["A local machine is lost or compromised post-flip; the attacker can forge signed events indefinitely because no revocation mechanism exists","REBAR_BOT_SIGNING_KEY leaks via a CI log; forged CI-authored events pass verify-identity"],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.25,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"no","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"moderate","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Story 5 (or a follow-on) must specify a monitoring/alerting mechanism for steady-state signing health (e.g., a scheduled `rebar verify-identity` job or CI canary that alerts if unsigned events appear post-flip), so regression from the enforced state is detected proactively rather than on the next push.","cohort":["T10"],"criteria":["T10"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Success Criteria only cover the pre-flip confirmation step ('confirmed by rebar verify-identity reporting them verified')","ABSENCE: no mention of ongoing alerting, dashboards, or scheduled verification runs after require_authenticated is set true"],"finding":"The plan has no post-flip observability mechanism to detect if a writer surface silently stops signing after enforcement is enabled — e.g., after a config reset, secret expiry, or VM redeploy wipes the key.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f3f2ba424d38de9b4","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Scope / planned child stories — Story 5 (The atomic flip) + Success Criteria","norm_id":"n72032572a078826c","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["A VM is redeployed without the signing key; review-bot writes unsigned events. The merge-gate catches the NEXT push, but hours of unsigned events exist with no alert.","REBAR_BOT_SIGNING_KEY expires/is rotated in GitHub but not updated; CI writes become unsigned silently until a human notices a red build."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.375,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Specify a concrete, findable handoff artifact for the anchor SHA between child 8d91 and child 8d39: e.g., a dedicated field on the 8d91 ticket, a config stub file committed in a branch, or a required structured comment format — so child 8d39 can unambiguously retrieve the exact SHA.","cohort":["G3","G4"],"criteria":["G4"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Child 8d91 AC bullet 3: 'The enforcement-boundary anchor commit SHA is chosen … and its rationale recorded on this ticket.'","Child 8d39 AC bullet 1: 'enforce_since … its value equals the exact anchor SHA documented by the grandfathering story (story 4).'","No shared config file, structured output, or formal ticket-link mechanism is specified for the handoff.","container pairing: parent + 1a51-b170-5168-46d2/4dc0-d003-c236-45de/79da-c7e4-8d7c-471d/8d39-85d7-8f34-45e6/8d91-5103-ae1b-44a7"],"finding":"The anchor SHA decided in child 8d91 is transmitted to child 8d39 solely via a human-recorded artifact on a ticket ('Record the chosen SHA + rationale on this ticket for the flip story to consume'). There is no formal inter-ticket link, structured field, or machine-readable handoff mechanism. This is an implicit shared state dependency with no contract enforcement — if 8d91 closes without a clearly findable SHA record, child 8d39 must hunt for or reconstruct it.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"ff8435ba5cf17ba44","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"child 8d91-5103-ae1b-44a7 AC bullet 3; child 8d39-85d7-8f34-45e6 AC bullet 1","norm_id":"nbf523ddb8f95155d","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["8d91 closes with the SHA buried in a comment; the operator working on 8d39 uses a different SHA from memory or a stale note — the wrong boundary is written atomically into production.","If the tickets-branch is rebased or SHA changes between stories, there is no automated check to catch the mismatch before the flip lands."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Add to child 8d91's AC: 'The SHA is recorded in a named, findable location — e.g., a ticket field, a pinned comment marked BOUNDARY_SHA=<value>, or a committed stub — that child 8d39 can reference unambiguously without free-text search.'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.25,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"no","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Assign closure/archival of parked idea a422 to one child story (e.g., the atomic-flip story 8d39 as the final step) or add a dedicated administrative AC to the parent: 'a422 is closed/archived and references this epic as its resolution.'","cohort":["G3","G4"],"criteria":["G4"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Parent plan: 'This epic supersedes a422 and drives the rollout to the point where identity.require_authenticated = true can be enabled with NOTHING failing on any writer surface.'","No child in the sibling roster (1a51, 4dc0, 79da, 8d39, 8d91) mentions closing or archiving a422.","container pairing: parent + 1a51-b170-5168-46d2/4dc0-d003-c236-45de/79da-c7e4-8d7c-471d/8d39-85d7-8f34-45e6/8d91-5103-ae1b-44a7"],"finding":"Parked idea a422 (dated-circular-velvetworm) is described in the parent plan as superseded by this epic, but no child story explicitly closes, archives, or formally supersedes a422. If a422 remains open or in a parked state, future operators may revisit it independently, creating duplicate effort, confusion about which epic is authoritative, or conflicting changes.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f986356df69063c07","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Parent plan Context section ('supersedes a422'); complete sibling roster","norm_id":"nfe6c2e864c43f40e","priority":0.0,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":["a422 remains open/parked; a future contributor picks it up and begins parallel work on local signing provisioning, duplicating or conflicting with 79da's changes.","The epic closes without a422 being archived; a status dashboard shows a422 as an open parked idea that misleads stakeholders about the state of the rollout."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Add to child 8d39's AC (as the last/wrap-up story): '[ ] Parked idea a422 (dated-circular-velvetworm) is closed/archived and its closure notes reference this epic as the resolution.'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.25,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"no","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Standardize all references to the config key as `identity.enforce_since` (fully qualified) throughout Context, Scope, and all AC bullets to eliminate any ambiguity about the config namespace.","cohort":["COH","E1"],"criteria":["E1"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":"novelty","evidence":["Context: 'the guardrail bug 27ae made the merge-gate config-driven and set an `enforce_since` grandfather boundary'","Scope story 4: 'verify/repin `identity.enforce_since`'","AC bullet 2: '`identity.enforce_since` is pinned to the enforcement-cutover commit'","AC bullet 4: 'the pinned `enforce_since`' (unqualified)"],"finding":"The term `enforce_since` is inconsistently qualified across sections: the Context uses bare 'enforce_since grandfather boundary' and AC bullet 4 uses 'the pinned `enforce_since`', while Story 4 and AC bullet 2 use the fully-qualified form '`identity.enforce_since`'. An implementer scanning for the config key to set may not realize all references are the same field.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fb7e6ecf2d1c99840","impact":0.264,"is_primary":null,"location":"Context (paragraph 4), Scope story 4, AC bullet 2, AC bullet 4","norm_id":"n39de13f53070b665","priority":0.132,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["Implementer configures a bare key `enforce_since` in the wrong config section instead of `identity.enforce_since`, causing silent misconfiguration."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Replace the bare 'enforce_since' in Context paragraph 4 and AC bullet 4 with the fully-qualified `identity.enforce_since` to match Story 4 and AC bullet 2.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.5,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add an explicit ordering dependency to child 8d91's scope/AC: the anchor SHA must be chosen only AFTER children 79da, 4dc0, and 1a51 have each produced at least one confirmed signed event — and this precondition should be stated in 8d91's acceptance criteria.","cohort":["G3","G4"],"criteria":["G4"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":"novelty","evidence":["Child 8d91 What section: 'Decide and document the enforcement-boundary anchor: an existing tickets-branch commit at which signing is confirmed live across all writers (NOT the flip commit).'","Child 8d91 Scope section: 'The grandfathering boundary check + a regression test + the boundary decision/rationale.' — no explicit dependency on 79da, 4dc0, 1a51.","Child 8d39 Scope: 'Depends on the local, GitHub Actions, Gerrit, and grandfathering stories' — only the flip story names its dependencies explicitly.","container pairing: parent + 1a51-b170-5168-46d2/4dc0-d003-c236-45de/79da-c7e4-8d7c-471d/8d39-85d7-8f34-45e6/8d91-5103-ae1b-44a7"],"finding":"Child 8d91 must select an anchor SHA from 'an existing tickets-branch commit at which signing is confirmed live across all writers,' but its own scope does not formally declare a dependency on children 79da, 4dc0, and 1a51 completing first. If 8d91 is worked in parallel with or before those signing stories, the 'all writers confirmed signing' precondition for anchor selection cannot be met, and 8d91 could close with an anchor SHA that predates confirmed multi-surface signing.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f6e89c817ab0325fb","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"child 8d91-5103-ae1b-44a7, What section ('Decide and document the enforcement-boundary anchor'); full sibling roster ordering","norm_id":"n4b4aaeb30574bfd2","priority":0.0,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["8d91 is started early (e.g., as a parallel track to unblock regression test authorship), closes with an anchor SHA from before local/CI/Gerrit signing is live, and 8d39 inherits that anchor — placing the enforcement boundary before any writer is confirmed signing.","A developer interprets 8d91's independence as license to run it before the signing stories, producing an anchor that doesn't satisfy the parent's sequencing requirement."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Add to child 8d91's AC: '[ ] The anchor SHA is chosen only after children 79da, 4dc0, and 1a51 have each produced a confirmed signed event (operator-attested), so the boundary point follows confirmed multi-surface signing.'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.625,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"medium","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}}],"impact_model_version":"plan-v3","material_fingerprint":"0fa0c4fbed1021d5","metrics":{"claim_path":"no-llm/no-network (structural; the fast claim check is a local HMAC verify)","det_ms":340.3,"llm_calls":22,"llm_ms":414498.7,"total_ms":414955.1,"verify_requests":13},"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","regver":"b293b9a55de591cc","runner":"pydantic_ai","schema":"plan_review_result_v2","ticket_id":"dc09-6565-cf85-4aea","ticket_type":"epic","verdict":"PASS","verified_at_sha":"d0f2d81a9e7b2cf3901dd7b7bc598d03f9d2d596"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"REVIEW_RESULT","timestamp":1784230225561796001,"uuid":"f07b3efe-28eb-4f2a-8949-a8ed75f5e392"}